laboratory_examinations.findings: The retrocecal appendix is mildly dilated, measuring up to 8-9 mm in diameter, with mild hyperemia of its wall. There is minimal periappendiceal fat stranding. Multiple subcentimeter lymph nodes are seen in the right lower quadrant, likely reactive. No hydronephrosis, upper abdominal free fluid, free air, or lymphadenopathy. Multiple subserosal fibroids within the uterus, measuring up to 5.4 x 3.4 cm on the right and 4.5 x 3.9 cm on the left. A small amount of pelvic free fluid is seen. Ovaries are unremarkable, and bladder is thin-walled.
